---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "2026-02-16";
const formattedDate = new Date(lastUpdated).toLocaleDateString("en-GB", { day: "numeric", month: "long", year: "numeric" });
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Sayr" description="Terms of Service for using the Sayr platform.">
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
		<div class="mb-12">
			<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground sm:text-4xl">Terms of Service</h1>
			<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Last updated: <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{formattedDate}</time></p>
			<p class="mt-4 text-lg text-muted-foreground">
				These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the Sayr platform operated by
				Doras Media Limited ("we", "us", "Sayr"). By creating an account or using Sayr, you agree to these Terms.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="space-y-12 text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">

			<!-- 1. The Service -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">1. The Service</h2>
				<p>
					Sayr is a collaborative project management platform available as a cloud-hosted service at sayr.io.
					These Terms apply exclusively to the cloud-hosted version of Sayr. Self-hosted deployments of Sayr are
					governed by the applicable software licence under which the source code is distributed.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 2. Eligibility -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">2. Eligibility</h2>
				<p>
					You must be at least 16 years of age to use Sayr. By creating an account, you represent that you meet
					this requirement. If you are using Sayr on behalf of an organisation, you represent that you have the
					authority to bind that organisation to these Terms.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 3. Accounts -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">3. Accounts</h2>
				<p>
					You sign in to Sayr using a third-party authentication provider (GitHub or Doras). You are responsible
					for maintaining the security of your authentication credentials and for all activity that occurs under
					your account.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					You must notify us promptly at{" "}
					<a href="mailto:support@sayr.io" class="text-foreground hover:underline">support@sayr.io</a>{" "}
					if you become aware of any unauthorised use of your account.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 4. Organisations & Members -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">4. Organisations & Members</h2>
				<p>
					Sayr allows you to create and manage organisations. As the owner or administrator of an organisation, you are
					responsible for:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
					<li>The actions of all members you invite to your organisation</li>
					<li>Managing roles, permissions, and access levels within your organisation</li>
					<li>Ensuring that members comply with these Terms</li>
					<li>Content published by your organisation, including public-facing tasks and projects</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="mt-2">
					If a member of your organisation violates these Terms, we may take action against the individual member,
					the organisation, or both, at our discretion.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 5. User Content -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">5. Your Content</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-foreground">You retain full ownership</strong> of all content you create on Sayr, including
					tasks, comments, attachments, labels, and any other materials ("Your Content"). We do not claim any intellectual
					property rights over Your Content.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					By using Sayr, you grant us a limited, non-exclusive, worldwide licence to host, store, display, and transmit
					Your Content solely for the purpose of operating and providing the service to you and your organisation. This
					licence ends when you delete Your Content or your account.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					Where you or your organisation mark content as "public", you acknowledge that it will be accessible to anyone
					with access to your organisation's public page. You are responsible for ensuring you have the right to make
					such content publicly available.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 6. Acceptable Use -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">6. Acceptable Use</h2>
				<p>You agree not to use Sayr to:</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
					<li>Violate any applicable law, regulation, or third-party right</li>
					<li>Upload or transmit malware, viruses, or other harmful code</li>
					<li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to our systems, other users' accounts, or data you are not authorised to access</li>
					<li>Interfere with or disrupt the integrity or performance of the service</li>
					<li>Scrape, crawl, or use automated means to extract data from Sayr beyond what is permitted by our API</li>
					<li>Use Sayr to send unsolicited communications (spam)</li>
					<li>Impersonate another person or entity</li>
					<li>Upload content that is unlawful, defamatory, obscene, or that infringes any intellectual property right</li>
					<li>Resell, redistribute, or sublicense access to Sayr without our prior written consent</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<!-- 7. Free & Paid Plans -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">7. Plans & Payment</h2>
				<p>
					Sayr offers both free and paid plans. The features available under each plan are described on our pricing page.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-2">7.1 Free Plan</h3>
				<p>
					The free plan is provided at our discretion and may be subject to usage limits. We reserve the right to modify
					the features or limits of the free plan at any time.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-2">7.2 Paid Plans</h3>
				<p>
					Payments for paid plans are processed by <strong class="text-foreground">Polar</strong> (Polar Software Inc.),
					which acts as our Merchant of Record. By subscribing to a paid plan, you also agree to{" "}
					<a href="https://polar.sh/legal/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-foreground hover:underline">Polar's terms</a>.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					Polar handles all billing, invoicing, tax collection, and payment processing on our behalf. Subscription terms,
					including billing cycles and cancellation, are managed through Polar.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-2">7.3 Changes to Pricing</h3>
				<p>
					We may change our pricing at any time. If you are on a paid plan, price changes will take effect at the start
					of your next billing cycle. We will provide reasonable notice of material price increases.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 8. API Usage -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">8. API Access</h2>
				<p>
					Sayr provides an API for programmatic access. API keys are tied to your account and you are responsible for
					keeping them secure. We may impose rate limits or usage restrictions on API access. Abuse of the API may
					result in throttling or termination of access.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 9. GitHub Integration -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">9. Third-Party Integrations</h2>
				<p>
					Sayr integrates with third-party services such as GitHub. When you connect a third-party service, you authorise
					us to access and process data from that service on your behalf, in accordance with the permissions you grant.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					Your use of third-party services is governed by their respective terms and privacy policies. We are not
					responsible for the practices of third-party service providers.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 10. Availability & Disclaimers -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">10. Service Availability & Disclaimers</h2>
				<p>
					Sayr is provided <strong class="text-foreground">"as is"</strong> and <strong class="text-foreground">"as available"</strong>,
					without warranties of any kind, whether express, implied, or statutory. We do not guarantee that the service will be
					uninterrupted, error-free, or secure.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					To the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, including but not limited to implied warranties
					of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					We may perform scheduled or unscheduled maintenance that results in temporary service interruptions. We will
					endeavour to provide notice of planned maintenance where possible.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 11. Limitation of Liability -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">11. Limitation of Liability</h2>
				<p>
					To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Doras Media Limited shall not be liable for any indirect,
					incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits, revenue, data, or business
					opportunity arising out of or related to your use of Sayr.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					Our total aggregate liability for any claims arising under these Terms shall not exceed the greater of (a) the
					amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim, or (b) EUR 100.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-2">
					Nothing in these Terms excludes or limits liability for death or personal injury caused by negligence, fraud,
					or any other liability that cannot be excluded or limited under Irish law.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 12. Termination -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">12. Termination</h2>

				<h3 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-2">12.1 By You</h3>
				<p>
					You may delete your account at any time. Upon deletion, your personal data will be removed in accordance with
					our <a href="/legal/privacy" class="text-foreground hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>. Content you contributed
					to an organisation may persist within that organisation's data unless the organisation owner also deletes it.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-2">12.2 By Us</h3>
				<p>We may suspend or terminate your account if you:</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
					<li>Violate these Terms or our Acceptable Use policy</li>
					<li>Engage in activity that is harmful to other users, our infrastructure, or third parties</li>
					<li>Use Sayr for any unlawful purpose</li>
					<li>Fail to pay applicable fees after reasonable notice</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="mt-2">
					Where possible, we will provide notice and an opportunity to remedy the violation before terminating your account.
					We reserve the right to terminate immediately in cases of severe or repeated violations.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground mt-6 mb-2">12.3 Effect of Termination</h3>
				<p>
					Upon termination, your right to access and use Sayr ceases immediately. Sections of these Terms that by their
					nature should survive termination (including Sections 5, 11, 13, and 14) will continue to apply.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 13. Governing Law -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">13. Governing Law & Disputes</h2>
				<p>
					These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Ireland, without regard to its conflict
					of law provisions. Any disputes arising under or in connection with these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive
					jurisdiction of the courts of Ireland.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 14. General -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">14. General Provisions</h2>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong class="text-foreground">Entire Agreement</strong> — These Terms, together with our{" "}
						<a href="/legal/privacy" class="text-foreground hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>, constitute the
						entire agreement between you and Doras Media Limited regarding Sayr.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong class="text-foreground">Severability</strong> — If any provision of these Terms is found to be
						unenforceable, the remaining provisions will continue in full force and effect.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong class="text-foreground">Waiver</strong> — Our failure to enforce any right or provision of these
						Terms shall not constitute a waiver of that right or provision.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong class="text-foreground">Assignment</strong> — You may not assign your rights or obligations under
						these Terms without our prior written consent. We may assign our rights and obligations without restriction.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong class="text-foreground">Amendments</strong> — We may update these Terms from time to time. When we
						make material changes, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page and, where appropriate,
						notify you via the platform or email. Your continued use of Sayr after changes take effect constitutes
						acceptance of the revised Terms.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<!-- 15. Contact -->
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">15. Contact Us</h2>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted/30 p-6">
					<p>
						<strong class="text-foreground">Doras Media Limited</strong><br />
						First Floor Penrose 2<br />
						Penrose Dock<br />
						Cork T23 YY09<br />
						Ireland
					</p>
					<p class="mt-2">
						Email:{" "}
						<a href="mailto:support@sayr.io" class="text-foreground hover:underline">support@sayr.io</a>
					</p>
					<p class="mt-4">
						See also:{" "}
						<a href="/legal/privacy" class="text-foreground hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>{" | "}
						<a href="/legal/subprocessors" class="text-foreground hover:underline">Subprocessors</a>
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
